name: Surskit
flavorText: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Masquerain
flavorText: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, shuffle an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their deck.

name: Froslass ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out, flip a coin. If heads, your opponent takes 1 fewer Prize card.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Pansage
flavorText: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Simisage
flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
Ability1Text: If you have Simisage, Simisear, and Simipour in play, ignore all Colorless Energy in the costs of attacks used by this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Pokémon that have an Ability, except any Simisage.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

name: Crustle
flavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 100 less damage from attacks from Evolution Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bounsweet
flavorText: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled- down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Steenee
flavorText: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Blipbug
flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dottler
flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Orbeetle
flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy card in your opponent's discard pile.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Nymble
flavorText: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it's in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Nymble
flavorText: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it's in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Attack1Text: Attach a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Attack2Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Toedscruel
flavorText: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.
Ability1Text: Cards in your opponent's discard pile can't be put into their hand by an effect of your opponent's Abilities or Trainer cards.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Wo-Chien
flavorText: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Grass Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon cost ColorlessColorless more.

name: Magby
flavorText: This Pokémon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day's fatigue.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 6 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Pansear
flavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Simisear
flavorText: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.
Ability1Text: If you have Simisage, Simisear, and Simipour in play, ignore all Colorless Energy in the costs of attacks used by this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Volcanion
flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
Attack1Text: Choose up to 2 of your Benched Pokémon and attach a Basic Fire Energy card from your discard pile to each of them.

name: Fuecoco
flavorText: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

name: Crocalor
flavorText: The combination of Crocalor's fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon's head.
Attack1Text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Armarouge ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has full HP, it takes 80 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Iron Moth
flavorText: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon's traits match up with an object described in an old book.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when this Pokémon moves from your Bench to the Active Spot, you may move any amount of Fire Energy from your other Pokémon to it.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Heat Ray.

name: Chi-Yu
flavorText: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Horsea
flavorText: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

name: Seadra
flavorText: Seadra's mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that's larger than the opening of its mouth.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Kingdra
flavorText: Scales shed by this Pokémon have such a splendorous gleam to them that they've been given to royalty as gifts.

name: Remoraid
flavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery

Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Feebas
flavorText: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Milotic
flavorText: It's said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you're feeling.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may use this Ability. Each player puts a Basic Pokémon from their discard pile onto their Bench. (Your opponent puts a Basic Pokémon onto their Bench first.)
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Fighting Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Garchomp ex
Attack1Text: Attach up to 3 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Mantyke

Attack1Text: Heal 120 damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Palkia
flavorText: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Panpour
flavorText: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Vanillite
flavorText: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.

name: Vanillish
flavorText: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it's a kind Pokémon.

name: Vanilluxe
flavorText: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Tsareena ex
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon until its remaining HP is 30.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon, and it recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Wimpod
flavorText: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy's presence.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Wimpod

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Golisopod
flavorText: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner's meal.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each card in your opponent's hand.

name: Golisopod ex
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, switch it with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Wiglett
flavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

name: Wiglett
flavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Veluza
flavorText: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

flavorText: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it's bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

flavorText: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

name: Chien-Pao

name: Mewtwo ex

name: Elekid

Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Iron Hands ex

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1.

name: Nacli

flavorText: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can't remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

name: Flamigo
flavorText: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

name: Slither Wing
flavorText: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

name: Zubat

Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

name: Liepard
flavorText: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.
Attack1Text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.
Attack1Text: Discard any number of Pokémon Tool cards from your hand. This attack does 50 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Thievul
flavorText: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may have your opponent reveal their hand, and then you choose 2 Energy cards you find there and shuffle them into your opponent's deck.

name: Morpeko
flavorText: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has no Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Move 2 Darkness Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Lokix
flavorText: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Brute Bonnet
flavorText: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.

name: Steelix
flavorText: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Jirachi
flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed's spikes grow big and strong.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokémon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Spinning Needles attack does 100 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Durant
flavorText: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on all of your Durant.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Honedge
flavorText: The blue eye on the sword's handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people's lives away.

name: Honedge

flavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

flavorText: Able to cut down anything with a single strike, it became known as the Fairy King's Sword, and it inspired awe in friend and foe alike.

name: Orthworm
flavorText: When attacked, this Pokémon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.

flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Porygon2

Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Porygon-Z
flavorText: Some say an additional program made this Pokémon evolve, but even academics can't agree on whether Porygon-Z is really an evolution.

name: Aipom

Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each card in your hand.

name: Miltank
flavorText: This Pokémon needs to be milked every day, or else it will fall ill. The flavor of Miltank milk changes with the seasons.

name: Whismur

name: Swablu

Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Tandemaus
